main event: A 35mm color slide showing a presumably unidentified flying object was reported from the New York World's Fair on May 30, 1965.
interesting points: The object was perfectly spherical, very luminescent, and surrounded by a purple halo., The object was not visible to the naked eye when the photo was taken., The photo analysis revealed no identifiable signature of the object., A request for analysis of the slide was made to Dr. J. Allen Hynek., The slide was initially thought to possibly show a UFO, but subsequent analysis indicated it might be a processing defect.
witness description: The sender was from Hempstead, New York and took the photo at the New York World's Fair.
